text: You're part of a space crew that was scheduled to rendezvous with another spacecraft on the bright surface of the moon. However, due to mechanical problems, your ship was forced to land about 200 miles from the rendezvous point. During re-entry and landing, most of the ship's equipment was damaged, and since survival depended on reaching the mother ship, the most critical items had to be selected to make the 200-mile journey.

Since survival depends on reaching the mother ship, the most critical items must be selected to complete the 200-mile journey. Below is a list of 15 items that need to be sorted from important to not important after landing
